					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just inspected how Nintendulator generates it's RGB palette (this is the one used in NESRGB when you choose the &quot;composite&quot; palette) and it worries me a bit that many colors fall outside of the RGB matrix (i.e. clipping).<br /><br />Here's the list, clipped values in red:<br /><br /><ul>00 = RGB(102, 102, 102)<br /><span style="color: #D0ACAC">01 = RGB(-24, 43, 155)</span><br />02 = RGB(17, 15, 193)<br /><span style="color: #D0C5C5">03 = RGB(64, -8, 188)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0B4B4">04 = RGB(103, -19, 143)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0B9B9">05 = RGB(124, -15, 69)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0BCBC">06 = RGB(121, 2, -14)</span><br /><span style="color: #D05454">07 = RGB(96, 28, -83)</span><br /><span style="color: #D01B1B">08 = RGB(55, 57, -121)</span><br /><span style="color: #D02222">09 = RGB(8, 80, -117)</span><br /><span style="color: #D06565">0A = RGB(-31, 91, -71)</span><br /><span style="color: #D08282">0B = RGB(-52, 87, 3)</span><br /><span style="color: #D08686">0C = RGB(-50, 70, 85)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0A4A4">0D = RGB(-30, -30, -30)</span><br />0E = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />0F = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />10 = RGB(174, 174, 174)<br />11 = RGB(7, 97, 245)<br /><span style="color: #D09696">12 = RGB(62, 59, 295)</span><br /><span style="color: #D09E9E">13 = RGB(124, 29, 290)</span><br />14 = RGB(176, 14, 230)<br />15 = RGB(204, 19, 131)<br />16 = RGB(201, 42, 21)<br /><span style="color: #D06666">17 = RGB(167, 77, -71)</span><br /><span style="color: #D01B1B">18 = RGB(112, 115, -121)</span><br /><span style="color: #D02424">19 = RGB(50, 145, -115)</span><br /><span style="color: #D07E7E">1A = RGB(-2, 160, -55)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0A4A4">1B = RGB(-30, 155, 43)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0A9A9">1C = RGB(-26, 132, 153)</span><br />1D = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />1E = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />1F = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />20 = RGB(256, 256, 256)<br /><span style="color: #D06464">21 = RGB(86, 178, 328)</span><br /><span style="color: #D01818">22 = RGB(142, 139, 379)</span><br /><span style="color: #D02121">23 = RGB(205, 108, 373)</span><br /><span style="color: #D07C7C">24 = RGB(258, 93, 312)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0A3A3">25 = RGB(286, 98, 212)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0A8A8">26 = RGB(283, 122, 101)</span><br />27 = RGB(249, 157, 7)<br /><span style="color: #D08E8E">28 = RGB(193, 196, -44)</span><br /><span style="color: #D09797">29 = RGB(130, 226, -38)</span><br />2A = RGB(77, 241, 23)<br />2B = RGB(49, 237, 122)<br />2C = RGB(52, 213, 234)<br />2D = RGB(79, 79, 79)<br />2E = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />2F = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />30 = RGB(256, 256, 256)<br /><span style="color: #D0A4A4">31 = RGB(186, 224, 286)</span><br /><span style="color: #D08585">32 = RGB(209, 208, 307)</span><br /><span style="color: #D08888">33 = RGB(235, 195, 304)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0AEAE">34 = RGB(257, 189, 279)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0BEBE">35 = RGB(268, 191, 238)</span><br /><span style="color: #D0C0C0">36 = RGB(267, 201, 192)</span><br />37 = RGB(253, 215, 154)<br />38 = RGB(230, 231, 133)<br />39 = RGB(204, 244, 135)<br />3A = RGB(183, 250, 160)<br />3B = RGB(171, 248, 201)<br />3C = RGB(172, 238, 247)<br />3D = RGB(183, 183, 183)<br />3E = RGB(0, 0, 0)<br />3F = RGB(0, 0, 0)</ul><br />And now when I think of it, isn't black supposed to be at RGB(16, 16, 16) and white at RGB(235, 235, 235) on a TV?</div>

